name: After Kanyike Edgar Kampala
description:
Kanyike Edgar is a dancer from Uganda who has run a residency program at Gudskul, collaborating with 32° East Kampala, Uganda as part of the 2020 KLA art lab program.
He also used it as an inspiration for his dance work. In his dance work, he tells of his findings and his journey in Jakarta. He also combines elements of traditional and contemporary Uganda dance.


00:15 seconds, 500x624 dimensions, stereo video drawing collage with instrumental dance audio.
